.TH MONITOR_THING 1 "2025-11-02" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
monitor_thing \- system monitoring utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B monitor_thing
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B monitor_thing
is a system monitoring utility that displays CPU usage statistics in real-time.
The utility continuously polls system metrics and displays them in a formatted table.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-poll\-rate " " \fIRATE\fR
Set the polling rate in seconds (default: 1).
Valid range is 1 to 3600 seconds.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Monitor CPU with default 1 second polling:
.B monitor_thing
.TP
Monitor CPU with 5 second polling interval:
.B monitor_thing \-p 5
.TP
Display help information:
.B monitor_thing \-\-help
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful program execution or help displayed.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (invalid arguments, out of range values, etc.).
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT
Gracefully shut down the monitoring loop and exit.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Kinetic Labs.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR top (1),
.BR htop (1),
.BR vmstat (8)
